NPC visual quest state indicator.
  Show a visual cue on the NPC (floating icon, stance change, colour shift) when new
  dialogue is available — i.e. when the NPC's state has advanced since the player last
  talked to them. Prevents players missing state transitions. Design TBD (icon above
  head vs. full stance animation). Blocked on art direction decision.

Art style direction (decide before sourcing assets).
  Kenney/cartoonish-cute vs dark-eldritch-serious — these need different asset sources.
  "Cute dog in a dark world" (Undertale contrast) is valid but intentional.
  Decision drives: character art, enemy art, UI skin, shader choices.

Level design + terrain.
  Currently both scenes are flat placeholder geometry. Needs real level design:
  platforms, obstacles, verticality to make movement abilities (dash, double jump,
  wall jump) feel purposeful. Blocked on: art direction, zone theme decisions.

Create angel wings item. (extra jump or extra glidy?)
Sword swing attack. (light, heavy, charge, spin?)
Dash move. (ground, air)
Dodge roll/invincibility frames.
Wall jump/wall slide.
