Sounds (in progress this session — foundation being laid)
  Deferred from audio session: footsteps (run state timer, surface detection),
  orb vacuum proximity hum (looping AudioStreamPlayer3D per orb while in range).
Animations
Enemies
Bug B — Stats resource is shared by reference, so health/stamina mutate the .tres file's in-memory object
  If you later add a mechanic that reduces health mid-session and then travel to another scene, the damage persists (which is correct for gameplay). But if you quit and relaunch,
  default_stats.tres only saves @export vars — health, stamina, level, and xp are plain vars, so they reset to 100/100/1/0 on every cold start. This is expected behavior for now,
  but means you have no save system yet — something to track.

Dark Souls-style stat investment system.
  Instead of automatic stat increases on level-up, award souls/points that the player spends at a hub NPC to invest in specific stats (strength, endurance, health, etc.).
  Current level-up auto-grants (+10 max HP, +5 max stamina, +2 regen) should be replaced or gated behind this system.

XP orb despawn without XP grant (design decision pending).
  Current behavior: orbs auto-collect (grant XP silently) after orb_lifetime seconds.
  Alternative: despawn without granting XP — creates tension to collect quickly but
  may feel punishing. Revisit once more zone content exists to judge pacing.

Death penalty — item/currency loss on death.
  Currently death preserves everything (XP, level, unlocks). Consider losing a portion
  of held currency or dropping items at the death location (DS1/DS3 style), once an
  inventory/currency system exists.

Weapon type system (Session B+).
  Distinct weapon classes (sword, axe, spell staff, ...) each scaling with a primary
  stat: Strength, Dexterity, or Intelligence. Dexterity and Intelligence not yet
  implemented as investable stats.

DS1-style weapon stat scaling (Session B+).
  Flat damage bonus = stat_value × weapon_scale_factor. Letter grades
  (S/A/B/C/D/E) map to scale factors (S ≈ 1.0 down to E ≈ 0.1), stored per weapon.
  Requires weapon type system above.

Strength stat combat wiring (Session B).
  PlayerStats.damage_multiplier field, set via invest_in_stat("strength").
  Wire into light_attack.gd and heavy_attack.gd: multiply config damage by
  stats.damage_multiplier. Add Strength row to StatAllocationScreen.

Stamina regen scaling.
  Regen rate does not change on level-up by design. Intended to be unlocked via
  an item or ability upgrade, not stat investment.

Dream — Session B visual upgrade.
  Replace DreamManager's placeholder CanvasLayer overlay with a full scene
  transition to dream_space.tscn (distinct shader, skybox). Only DreamManager
  needs to change — stat allocation screen and PlayerStats are untouched.

Auto-restore last scene on cold start (DS1-style load-in).
  SaveManager stores last_scene but the game always boots into hub. True DS1 feel would
  auto-travel to last_scene on load. Requires hub to act as a boot/loading pass-through.
  Design decision needed: what does "last safe point" mean — last portal used, last rest
  site, or literally last position? Depends on checkpoint system design.
  Also requires saving last known Vector3 position and restoring it via spawn point system.